elled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Regular, deeply incised letters, of which alpha the widest. Borken bar alpha; epsilon has shorter middle bar; Mu has vertical first and last, with middle strokes only descending half-way; omicron is small and mid-line; rho is rounded and closed; sigma is regular four bar, with horizontal top and bottom, middle strokes half-width.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Line 1-2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"10\" atMost=\"15\">10-15\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462487\">Segesta\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523171\">Segesta\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.94171, 12.83649\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0200\" notAfter-